  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Gingival inflammation has been associated with cardiovascular diseases, including heart
      attack and stroke, because of elevation of blood risk markers such as cholesterol, glucose
      and C reactive protein. The treatment of gingival diseases decreases the concentration of
      these risk factors in the blood of cardiovascular patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
